**Exploring class loading issues**\\n\\nI'm considering whether a commit is needed; perhaps we do have one. The direct import of `AntClassLoader2` in my test might be triggering class loading, but it doesn’t call `defineClassFromData`. I'm also thinking maybe the tests run with coverage that avoids throwing exceptions. If there's a catch for `ClassFormatError`, then it should be handled differently. I could implement a subclass to call the protected method directly with invalid class data, using `assertThatThrownBy` or a try-catch to avoid issues in native.\"}]}"}, {"type": "toolCall", "id": "call_1OC3LZ8Z3ITJ64I0BldxW1P5|fc_06f2b3a4515672e70169eff36efc80819d86f4565e628d4816", "name": "read", "arguments": {"path": "metadata/ant/ant/1.6/reachability-metadata.json", "limit": 200}}], "api": "openai-responses", "provider": "OCA", "model": "gpt-5.5", "usage": {"input": 1662, "output": 1529, "cacheRead": 30720, "cacheWrite": 0, "totalTokens": 33911, "cost": {"input": 0, "output": 0, "cacheRead": 0, "cacheWrite": 0, "total": 0}}, "stopReason": "toolUse", "timestamp": 1777333079503, "responseId": "resp_06f2b3a4515672e70169eff357fb58819db606f7010ac5cbfe"}, "toolResults": [{"role": "toolResult", "toolCallId": "call_1OC3LZ8Z3ITJ64I0BldxW1P5|fc_06f2b3a4515672e70169eff36efc80819d86f4565e628d4816", "toolName": "read", "content": [{"type": "text", "text": "{\n  \"reflection\": [\n    {\n      \"condition\": {\n        \"typeReached\": \"org.apache.tools.ant.util.regexp.RegexpMatcherFactory\"\n      },\n      \"type\": \"org.apache.tools.ant.util.regexp.Jdk14RegexpMatcher\",\n      \"methods\": [\n        {\n          \"name\": \"<init>\",\n          \"parameterTypes\": []\n        }\n      ]\n    }\n  ]\n}\n"}], "isError": false, "timestamp": 1777333103330}]}
