[thinking] **Considering package-private access**
[thinking] 
[thinking] It seems like there's a question about whether generating a helper class at runtime in a library package, but not in the test source package, violates some rules. It likely does because tests shouldn’t appear in the same package. The runtime-generated helper might be an exception, but it shouldn’t require reflection. Also, if a class is created in the same package and loaded by the same classloader, it can access package-private methods. Would using JavaCompiler help with this situation?
